<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content=
        "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title> Survey Form </title>
  <style>
    *,
    *::before,
    *::after {
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
        font-family: verdana;
        width: 80%;
        height: 100% auto;
        margin: auto;
        color: white;
        padding-left: 13%;
        padding-right: 13%;
    }

    body::before {
        content: '';
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        height: 100%;
        width: 100%;
        margin: auto;
        z-index: -1;
        background: rgb(0,0,0);
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%, rgba(20,9,6,1) 49%, rgba(104,4,4,1) 100%);
        background-size: cover;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-position: center;
    }


    p {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
    }

    .container {
        margin: 20px ;
    }

    .form-group {
        font-size: 20px;
        padding: 10px;
        margin: auto;
        display: block;
        text-align: center;
        width: 250px;
    }

    .form-control {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: 30px;
        color: #999999;
        border: 1px solid;
        border-radius: 5px;
        margin: auto;
        padding-left: 10px;
        }
    main {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        padding: 20px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        border-radius: 25px;
        z-index: 2;
        position: relative;
        box-shadow: 0px -1px 10px 5px white;
        line-height: 25px;
    }

    .input-radio {
        display: block;
        margin: 15px;
        left: 10px;
    }

    .optional {
        font-size: 12px;
    }

    #number {
        width: 84px;
    }

    #title {
        text-align: center;
    }

    legend {
        font-size: 19px;
        font-weight: bold;
    }

    .clue {
        font-size: 14px;
    }

    #comments {
        width: 70%;
        height: 200px;
    }

    .form-group1 {
        display: block;
        padding: 10px;
        margin: auto;
        text-align: center;
        width: 80%;
    }

    .form-group2 {
        display: block;
        padding: 10px;
        margin: auto;
        text-align: center;
    }

    button {
        width: 100px;
        height: 30px;
    }
    </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <header>
   <div class="container">
    <h1 id="title">Survey Form</h1>
     <p id="description">Hi there! Thanks for stopping by! </p>
    <p>With this poll we want to find out how the general public views <strong>MAGIC</strong> in <strong>2021</strong>.</p>
  </header>
  <main>
    
     <form id="survey-form">
     <div class="form-group">
       <label id="name-label" for="name">Name</label>
       <input type="text" name="name" id="name" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter your name" required />
     </div>
       
     <div class="form-group">
       <label id="email-label" for="email">Email</label>
       <input type="email" name="email" id="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter your email" required/>
     </div>
       
     <div class="form-group">
      <label id="number-label" for="number"
        >Age</label>
      <input type="number" name="age" id="number" min="8" max="99" class="form-control" placeholder="Select" />
    </div>
       
     <div class="form-group1">
        <p id="dropdown1">    Have you ever seen a live magic trick?</p>
        <select id="dropdown" name="trick" class="form-control" required>
          <option disabled selected value>Choose one from below</option>
          <option value="yes">Yes</option>
          <option value="yes2">Yes,but long time ago</option>
          <option value="no">No</option>
        </select>
     </div>
    <br/>
     <fieldset>
          <legend>What comes to your mind when thinking about magic? </legend>
          <input type="radio" name="action"  id="definitely" value="yes1" /><label for="definitely">As something that seems impossible, which has a scientific explanation that is kept secret.</label><br />
          <input type="radio" name="action" id="maybe" value="yes2"  /><label for="maybe">As a paranormal event, something science can not explain. </label><br />
          <input type="radio" name="action" id="not-sure" value="no1" /><label for="not-sure">Other, please specify</label><br/>
             <textarea rows="2" cols="50" ></textarea>
      </fieldset>
     <br/>
       
     <div class="form-group2">
      <p>
        Which magic trick is your favourite?
        <span class="clue">(Check all that apply)</span>
      </p>
       <label><input name="prefer" value="production" type="checkbox" class="input-checkbox" /><strong>Production - </strong> The magician makes something appear out of thin air, like pulling a rabbit out of an empty top hat.</label>
          <br/>
          <br/>
      <label>
        <input name="prefer" value="vanishing" type="checkbox" class="input-checkbox" /><strong>Vanishing - </strong> This is when the magician makes something or someone disappear. The ball that appears to vanish in mid-air is a common example.</label>
         <br/>
         <br/>
      <label>
       <input name="prefer" value="transformation" type="checkbox" class="input-checkbox" /><strong>Transformation - </strong> The magician alters an object’s form or properties, such as changing a flower’s color or transforming a dollar bill into a dove.</label>
          <br/>
          <br/>
      <label>
        <input name="prefer" value="restoration" type="checkbox" class="input-checkbox" /><strong>Restoration - </strong>Examples include cutting an assistant in half or tearing a piece of paper, and then making them whole again.</label>
          <br/>
          <br/>
      <label>
        <input name="prefer" value="levitation" type="checkbox" class="input-checkbox" /><strong>Levitation - </strong> Defying gravity, the magician makes something or someone appear to levitate.</label>

    <div class="form-group2">
        <p>Any comments or suggestions?</p>
        <textarea
          id="comments" class="input-textarea" name="comment" placeholder="Enter your comment here...">
        </textarea>
    </div>
    </div>
     <div class="form-group">
          <button type="submit" id="submit" class="submit-button">
            Submit </button>
      </div>
     </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>